{{nonprofit-org-stub}} {{Infobox Organization |name = Openlands |image = |formation = 1963 |type = [[Non-profit organization]] |purpose = Preservation and development of recreation and conservation resources |headquarters = Chicago, IL |coords = |region_served = Chicago area |leader_title = President |leader_name = Gerald Adelmann |main_organ = Board of Directors |website = [https://openlands.org/ openlands.org] }}
Starting in 1963, then known as Openlands Project, '''Openlands''' is a [[non-profit]] that works with groups and individuals in northeastern [[Illinois]] to preserve open space, develop walking and biking trails, restore natural areas, and connect people to the outdoors. It is a member of [[Chicago Wilderness]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Chicago Wilderness members|url=http://www.chicagowilderness.org/?page=MemberDirectory|publisher=Chicago Wilderness|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>
In 1978 the Corporation for Open Lands (CorLands) was started as an affiliate of Openlands. In 1982 the Canal Corridor Association was formed by Openlands to create the first [[National Heritage Corridor]] along the old [[Illinois and Michigan Canal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Openlands Project|url=http://www.encyclopedia.chicagohistory.org/pages/932.html|publisher=Encyclopedia of Chicago|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref> The Openlands Lakeshore Preserve in [[Fort Sheridan, Illinois|Fort Sheridan]] was created in 2011, encompassing ravines and bluffs along the shore of Lake Michigan.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ravines, bluffs and art await|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/09/08/ravines-bluffs-and-art-aw_n_953761.html|publisher=Huffingtion Post|accessdate=20 December 2017}}</ref> In 2012 the [[Hackmatack National Wildlife Refuge]] was officially started with a 12-acre donation from Openlands.<ref>{{cite web|title=Five years of Hackmatack NWR|url=https://www.fws.gov/midwest/news/BdayHackmatack.html|publisher=US Fish & Wildlife Service|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>
In 2017 Conserve Lake County (serving Lake County, IL) merged with Openlands.<ref>{{cite web|title=Merger will strengthen conservation efforts|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/news/20171201/merger-will-strengthen-conservation-efforts-in-lake-county|publisher=Daily Herald|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>
